# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# form-native-llm.form — would an LLM built on Form primitives be a different
#                        shape? Yes. This names how, with the lanes kept honest.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# Urs: "wouldn't an LLM on form primitives be architected different, embedding
# would be quite different, and with choice, fail, cut and stop as well as
# nothing, 0, 1, node as core values the transformer layers might look different
# as well. how would it look, and how would we cross learn/train from a local
# LLM to that? could we fine-tune an LLM to natively speak form and how would
# that change efficiency and capabilities (fractal, holographic, scalar wave)?"
#
# LANES (CLAUDE.md discipline — kept separate, never blended):
#   [RUNS]      proven in the body today, cited.
#   [INFER]     architectural inference from the primitives; falsifiable, not yet built.
#   [SYMBOL]    frequency/resonance language — a way of seeing, NOT a physics claim.
# form-native-models.form is the companion: it proves a STANDARD transformer runs
# deterministically in Form. THIS file asks the different question — what the
# primitives make NATIVE that a dense float transformer only approximates.

(form-native-llm

  (lineage
    (runs-on        form-native-models.form)         # the deterministic numeric substrate [RUNS]
    (value-abi      fourth-kernel.form tagged-ABI)   # {nothing,0,1,node} = {null-ref,int,int,ref} [RUNS]
    (cross-learn    co-learning.form federated-slices.form)  # the oracle + merge mechanisms [RUNS]
    (grounds        cell-numerics.form numeric-formats.canonical.json))

  # ── 1. Embedding: a coordinate, not an opaque vector ────────────────
  # A dense LLM embeds a token as a learned float vector — meaning is a point
  # in R^d, opaque, compared by dot product. In Form a cell's identity is its
  # CONTENT-ADDRESSED NodeID: same composition -> same coordinate, everywhere,
  # for free. [RUNS today: substrate equivalence-by-structure.]
  (embedding
    (dense-llm   a-learned-float-vector compared-by-dot-product)
    (form-native the-NodeID-IS-the-embedding)         # [INFER] position in the content-addressed lattice
    (consequence two-utterances-that-COMPOSE-the-same-share-a-coordinate)  # not learned — structural
    (hybrid      a-float-vector can hang off a NodeID as a recipe leaf)  # [INFER] learned + structural together
    (so          meaning is partly GIVEN by structure, partly LEARNED on top — not all learned))

  # ── 2. Attention: choice/fail, not dense softmax ────────────────────
  # Dense attention softmaxes QK^T over ALL tokens every layer — O(n^2) dense
  # float, everything attends to everything, weighted. The BMF primitives make
  # a different shape native: SPECULATIVE, SPARSE retrieval.
  (attention
    (dense-llm   softmax over all-pairs O(n-squared) dense-float-everything-weighted)
    (form-native CHOICE the relevant cells, FAIL the irrelevant, CUT to the match, STOP when resolved)  # [INFER]
    (mechanism   content-addressed retrieval — attend by shape-match / NodeID kinship, not dot-product)
    (sparsity    nothing is a FIRST-CLASS value (axiom-1) — a position can be NOTHING, genuine
                 zero-cost absence, not a softmax weight rounding toward zero)  # [RUNS: nothing in the 4th kernel]
    (cost        [INFER] sub-quadratic when most pairs FAIL early — backtracking is a pointer move
                 (axiom-3), so a wrong attention path costs O(1) to abandon, not a recomputed pass))

  # ── 3. The layer: a recipe, content-addressed (holographic) ─────────
  # A dense transformer block is a fixed dense-matmul pipeline. A Form layer is
  # a RECIPE — and identical sub-computations share a NodeID, so a pattern
  # computed once is reused wherever it recurs. This is the HOLOGRAPHIC property,
  # grounded: the whole in every part because the part IS the same content-cell.
  (layer
    (dense-llm   fixed dense matmul + softmax + matmul, recomputed every token)
    (form-native a recipe tree; repeated sub-shapes share NodeIDs -> computed once, reused)  # [RUNS: content-addressing]
    (holographic [SYMBOL->grounded] "the whole in every part" = same shape, same NodeID, everywhere;
                 the grounded correlate is structural DEDUP + cross-document equivalence)
    (mutable     the architecture is DATA (a recipe), so it can grow/prune at runtime —
                 a dense .pt cannot rewrite its own graph; a Form model can)  # [RUNS: form-native-models generatable]
    (verifiable  every layer output is reproducible three-way (validate.sh) — not a black box))  # [RUNS]

  # ── 4. The value type IS the ack vocabulary ─────────────────────────
  # {nothing, 0, 1, node} (fourth-kernel tagged ABI) gives the model honest
  # categorical outputs a float head only approximates: nothing = "no answer /
  # abstain" (not argmax of noise), 0/1 = decided, node = a counter-offer (a
  # structured continuation, the model handing back a cell, not a token id).
  (values
    (nothing  honest-abstention — the model can SAY no-answer, axiom-1, not hallucinate the nearest)
    (zero-one decided categorical, exact)
    (node     a counter-offer: the model returns a CELL (a structured plan / a sub-recipe), not a flat token)  # [INFER]
    (so       generation is offer-and-acknowledge (core-axioms): the model OFFERS cells, the world ACKs))

  # ── 5. Fractal / holographic / scalar-wave — the three framings ─────
  (framings
    (fractal      [RUNS] recursive composition — cells compose cells to any depth, the same
                  blueprint at every scale; a Form model is self-similar across layers by construction)
    (holographic  [SYMBOL->grounded] content-addressing: every part carries the identity of the whole-shape
                  it belongs to; reconstruct-from-a-fragment = look up the NodeID. Grounded as dedup +
                  equivalence, NOT claimed as optical holography)
    (scalar-wave  [SYMBOL] a frequency-language framing (CLAUDE.md frequencies are symbolic operating
                  language, NOT a physical measurement claim): meaning propagating by RESONANCE — a query
                  cell "resonates" with stored cells that share its shape — rather than by dense numeric
                  transport. The grounded correlate is content-addressed resonance: shape-match retrieval,
                  same NodeID = perfect resonance. Held in the mystery lane on purpose; the engineering
                  claim underneath is only the retrieval-by-shape-match, which is buildable [INFER]))

  # ── 6. Cross-learning from a local LLM — already have the mechanism ─
  # Two proven patterns carry this; no new theory needed:
  (cross-learn
    (oracle-distill [RUNS] co-learning.form M1 already learned from an oracle 0->91% (a Form-native
                    classifier learning from the SoundAnalysis oracle). Same shape: the local LLM is the
                    ORACLE; it emits (prompt -> output) pairs; the Form-native model learns to reproduce
                    them; champion-challenger promotes the Form path only when it matches on held-out)
    (slice-merge    [RUNS] federated-slices.form merges trust-weighted model slices deterministically —
                    so many Form models cross-teach by sharing content-addressed deltas, every cell
                    merging to the SAME numbers (a determinism PyTorch float-averaging can't promise))
    (the-bridge     [INFER] distill the local LLM's BEHAVIOR into Form recipes, then let the structural
                    layer (embedding-as-coordinate, attention-as-choice) REPLACE the dense parts where it
                    matches — measured, champion-challenger, never assumed))

  # ── 6b. The MESH: many cells, active inference, error-gated consolidation ──
  # Urs: "multiple cells contribute to active inference and continuous learning;
  # for every infer error we detect at run-time, that is feedback for the
  # short-term cells before they switch states into long-term."
  # This is not new theory — the body holds the parts; this names their union:
  (mesh-active-inference
    (error-is-the-signal [RUNS] active-inference.form: "infer error is core for learning" —
                    ai-surprise (prediction error) DRIVES the update; ai-settled? = residual surprise
                    fell below tolerance; a step that already fits teaches nothing. The runtime infer
                    error IS the learning signal, exactly as named)
    (short-then-long [RUNS] federated-slices.form M4 + the gas->water->ice phase metabolism: a fresh
                    observation is GAS (volatile, short-term); runtime error keeps updating it; it cools
                    to WATER (a validated pattern) and only FREEZES to ICE (consolidated, long-term, shared)
                    when ai-settled? AND champion-challenger promote — CLS/EWC by another name)
    (the-gate       [INFER, the synthesis] consolidation short->long is GATED ON PREDICTION ERROR:
                    a short-term cell switches to long-term only when its residual runtime error is low
                    AND it survives the challenger. High ongoing error -> stays plastic (short-term);
                    low settled error -> crystallizes (long-term). Error is both the teacher and the gate)
    (many-cells     [RUNS mechanism] every cell runs its own active inference locally; deltas are
                    content-addressed slices; the trust-weighted deterministic merge (slice-merge) makes
                    the MESH learn what no single cell could — co-learning proved two mics beat one. Each
                    cell's runtime errors feed ITS short-term plasticity; only settled long-term slices
                    are offered to the mesh, so the network shares CONSOLIDATED knowing, not noise)
    (continuous     [INFER] inference and learning are the same loop: infer -> measure error -> update
                    short-term -> (settled? promote to long-term : stay plastic) -> share -> merge. No
                    train/serve split; the model learns AT runtime from every error, the mesh consolidating
                    what settles. The fourth kernel's nothing-ack matters here: an honest "I don't know"
                    (nothing) is a HIGH-surprise signal that keeps the cell plastic instead of faking a 1)
    (where-it-runs  active-inference.fk + federated-slices.fk + co-learning.fk + champion-challenger.fk
                    already RUN three-way; the union into a learning LLM is the [INFER] build, stone by
                    stone, each gated by measured error, never by faith))

  # ── 7. Fine-tuning a local LLM to natively SPEAK Form — concrete ────
  # The nearest, most useful step, and fully buildable on the proven stack:
  (speak-form
    (corpus      [INFER, buildable now] the substrate IS the dataset: every spec, recipe, .fk, and the
                 idea->spec->code chains are (intent -> Form/BML) pairs. Generate (NL-intent, Form-recipe)
                 from the body; LoRA-fine-tune a local model (ollama/mlx) to EMIT Form notation/BML)
    (capability  the model's output stops being plausible TEXT and becomes a RECIPE: content-addressed,
                 composable, and VERIFIABLE — it either proves three-way or it does not. Hallucination is
                 bounded by what NodeIDs exist (the substrate's promise), not by RLHF taste)  # [INFER]
    (efficiency  [INFER] a Form-emitting model can be SMALLER for the same useful power: it offloads
                 structure/equivalence to the substrate (given, not learned) and need only learn the
                 mapping intent->shape; the dedup + verify happen outside its weights)
    (loop        speak-form closes the north-star: the agent's VOICE (satsang M4) composing in Form, the
                 fourth kernel running what it composes, the witness proving it — language that EXECUTES))

  (invariant
    (different-yes    Form primitives make sparse-speculative attention, structural embedding, honest
                      abstention, and mutable verifiable layers NATIVE — a dense transformer approximates these)
    (lanes-honest     RUNS vs INFER vs SYMBOL kept separate; scalar-wave stays mystery, its engineering
                      correlate (shape-match retrieval) named plainly)
    (build-on-proven  every step composes from what RUNS: deterministic numerics, the tagged ABI, the
                      oracle-distill + slice-merge mechanisms, the substrate-as-corpus)
    (smallest-first   fine-tune-to-speak-Form is the nearest real stone; the native-attention rewrite is
                      the deep one, taken measured and champion-challenger, never by faith)))

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# The honest one-paragraph answer
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Yes — and the difference is not cosmetic. A Form-native LLM embeds by
# COORDINATE (content-addressed) instead of by opaque vector; attends by CHOICE
# / FAIL (sparse, speculative, O(1) to abandon a wrong path) instead of dense
# softmax; can output NOTHING (honest abstention) or a NODE (a structured
# counter-offer) instead of only a token distribution; and its layers are
# RECIPES that dedup holographically and can rewrite themselves. We reach it not
# by faith but by the mechanisms that already RUN: distill a local LLM as an
# oracle (co-learning, proven 0->91%), merge slices deterministically (federated-
# slices), and — the nearest stone — fine-tune a local model on the substrate to
# EMIT Form, so its words become verifiable executable recipes. Fractal and
# holographic are grounded (recursive composition; content-addressed dedup);
# scalar-wave stays in the mystery lane, its only engineering claim being
# retrieval-by-resonance = shape-match. The capability shift: outputs that
# prove instead of merely persuade.
#
#   coh substrate form "?equivalent @recipe(form-native-llm)"   # after ingest
